Laterality –intraindividual differences that occur in either side but are consistent
between the sides

Conclusion
Transcriptomic data indicate the existence of
intra-individual lateral differences between the
carotid bodies.
These differences are not linked to a specific side of
the body suggesting CB laterality but not sidedness.
